        <article>
          <p>My name is Ganis Angger Atmawarin. I'm a Jogja based pirate wannabe who can spotted most of the time around kitchen, doing some food plundering as manly as possible. Most of my prey would called me Pemangsa, but my ally would carefully address me as Ganis. I was born, raised, and probably drinking too much sun in the eastern corner of Indonesia, Sorong. Now I'm living in Jakarta, the ever bustling city, the capital of Indonesia, where the attraction and irritation is amusingly equal.</p>
          <p>What I'm doing? Well, when I’m not busy declarin’ war on food, or twitting my goddamn parrot, you can find me working full time as a web designer, writing an occasional things here and there, trying to intimidate people into donating their money for my weekly pudding Friday.</p>
          <p>I designed this site on a scrap paper and build it with Illustrator, Photoshop, Sublime Text 2 & Compass. I use the power of ExpressionEngine to lighten the content, Typekit to serve the tasty typeface, and SCSS - Foundation to do some of layout heavy lifting.</p>
          <p>For the top navigation, I pick the stingy gentleman Alternate Gothic 2 by Morris Fuller Benton. I use the combination of Franklin Gothic and SchoolBook Web for entry navigation and footer - still courtesy of Benton. The body copy typography is subject to change depending on my mood, my prey flavour of the day and the sun stars relative position toward the moon.</p>
          <p>Content wise, I want to set it as my playground on story telling & typographic experiment. I write the content in English, but on a few occassion, you’ll find Indonesian. Some of the articles that I write contains materials that people may find as terribly offensive or incredibly arousing. So remember, whatever happen when you read it, keep your pants on.</p>
          <p>All material created by me, Ganis Angger Atmawarin, unless otherwise noted. But, you are allowed to copy, distribute, or display your derivative copy of my works without my permission (some pudding would be nice though).</p>
          <p>I don't do commenting system, but you can say hi at contact page.</p>
        </article>
